100. asyncio
asyncio is Python's built-in library for asynchronous programming.
It helps run multiple tasks concurrently without creating multiple threads.

import asyncio
async def task():
    print("Running")
asyncio.run(task())

Real-Time Example: Suppose a website needs to:
Fetch user profile
Fetch orders
Fetch notifications
All can run concurrently using asyncio.














































































































































